President Donald Trump has announced his intention to nominate several individuals to key positions in his administration. Ann Marie Buerkle of New York is nominated to be the Chairman of the Consumer Product Safety Commission and a Commissioner of the Consumer Product Safety Commission. She has previously served as a Commissioner and Acting Chair of the Consumer Product Safety Commission, as well as a United States Representative and Assistant Attorney General for the state of New York.

Peter Hoekstra of Michigan is nominated to be the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Kingdom of the Netherlands. He has previously served as a member of Congress, Chairman of the House Permanent Select Committee on Intelligence, and has been involved in public policy and business affairs.

Justin Hicks Siberell of Maryland is nominated to be the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Kingdom of Bahrain. He is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and has extensive experience in the Middle East and Gulf States.

Christopher Krebs of Virginia is appointed to the Department of Homeland Security as the Assistant Secretary for Infrastructure Protection. He has experience in critical infrastructure protection and cybersecurity risk management, having served as Senior Counselor to the Secretary of Homeland Security and Director for Cybersecurity Policy at Microsoft.

These nominations and appointments reflect President Trump's choices for key positions in his administration.